text: In this day & age of media accessibility one would think a group as large as @FedEx would actually deliver on time. Thanks for ruining my company launch. Package is *only* 3 days late. And now the (expected) run around had been dispensed by employees who don't know jack.

@Veruca72 Hello, this is Robin. I apologize for your experience. I will be happy to look into your concerns. Please DM your name, address, city, state, zip code, tracking number, phone number, and email address. https://t.co/7vnSkvqx3r

@FedExHelp There's no help available. All I'll get is my $31shipping. Event is ruined. It starts in 35 min & my package still is not delivered. Y'all just called me - after 3 calls in to you - to tell me....wait for it...that my PACKAGE IS ON THE TRUCK FOR DELIVERY TODAY. LOL. #Derp

@FedExHelp Was supposed to be delivered the 22nd. Only a *little* bit late. All my branded shirts, hats, uniforms & logo'd hand outs and brochures are in that package. Red hot mad. Screwing the little guy once again. I should have used @UPS .
@Veruca72 I apologize for your experience and regret the effect it had on your company launch.  ~ Robin
@FedExHelp You don't regret anything. It had no impact on you. I'm small fry. You don't * really* care.
